{"bookmarked": 5, "bucket_name": "Today", "bucket_order": 3, "change_log": [{"anon": "stud", "data": "jugjg22dc7k4hq", "type": "create", "uid_a": "a_0", "when": "2019-04-14T06:18:28Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "jugjg2295824hp", "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_1", "when": "2019-04-14T06:29:57Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "jugjg2295824hp", "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_0", "when": "2019-04-14T06:34:53Z"}, {"anon": "no", "to": "jugjg2295824hp", "type": "followup", "uid": "is6p6unggda5ox", "when": "2019-04-14T08:02:11Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "jugjg2295824hp", "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_1", "when": "2019-04-14T08:02:45Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "to": "jugjg2295824hp", "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_0", "when": "2019-04-14T08:18:19Z"}], "children": [{"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 4/7 - 4/13", "bucket_order": 50, "children": [{"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 4/7 - 4/13", "bucket_order": 50, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T06:34:53Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jugk163dfu1213", "subject": "<p>Np, good luck to you as well :)</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_0", "updated": "2019-04-14T06:34:53Z"}], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T06:29:57Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jugjutemhqi3mg", "no_answer": 0, "no_upvotes": 0, "subject": "<p>Thank you so much! Good luck with all your future job-huntings!!!</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "followup", "uid_a": "a_1", "updated": "2019-04-14T06:29:57Z"}, {"anon": "no", "bucket_name": "Week 4/7 - 4/13", "bucket_order": 50, "children": [{"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 4/7 - 4/13", "bucket_order": 50, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T08:02:45Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jugn662fvs6411", "subject": "&#43;2^100&#xff01;", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_1", "updated": "2019-04-14T08:02:45Z"}, {"anon": "stud", "bucket_name": "Week 4/7 - 4/13", "bucket_order": 50, "children": [], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T08:18:19Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jugnq6u4rre7a9", "subject": "<p>Thanks,\u00a0Farid! Appreciate your posts as they helped me so just wanted to pay it forward :)</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "feedback", "uid_a": "a_0", "updated": "2019-04-14T08:18:19Z"}], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T08:02:11Z", "data": {"embed_links": null}, "folders": [], "id": "jugn5fx4qjy3oz", "no_answer": 0, "no_upvotes": 0, "subject": "<p>What a beast! And spreading positivity and the wealth? You\u2019re making the culture at Berkeley so much better by making this post. We\u2019re all one big family in the CS department, including alumni and future students. Helping each other is amazing.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Youre going to have a wonderful time at your internship!</p>", "tag_good": [], "tag_good_arr": [], "type": "followup", "uid": "is6p6unggda5ox", "updated": "2019-04-14T08:02:11Z"}], "config": {}, "created": "2019-04-14T06:18:28Z", "data": {"embed_links": []}, "default_anonymity": "no", "drafts": null, "folders": ["other"], "history": [{"anon": "stud", "content": "<p>(Inspired by Farid)</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I see a lot of posts on this Piazza talking about how they have trouble landing an internship or even a full-time job in their desired field. Just wanted to share my personal\u00a0experience and some advice that may be helpful.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>I&#39;ve been searching since September for an internship and as a junior, this would technically be my &#34;last&#34; chance before full-time recruiting starts in the Fall this year. I was getting rejected from everywhere.\u00a0For ~50% of my apps, I didn&#39;t even receive a response. I used Handshake, LinkedIn, Google, referrals, and other sources, sending out over 150 apps. Around February, I started getting really desperate. As Albert Einstein said, &#34;The definition of insanity is doing the same thing over and over again, but expecting different results&#34;. So I changed my strategy, revamped my resume, and set some time every day to review the fundamentals, prep hard,\u00a0do mock interviews, review my mistakes in past interviews, and yes, even apply to internships that late. I had to make sacrifices in terms of my academics and social life but it was well worth it. And the offers I got actually all came from apps I sent out after February. So there&#39;s still hope for all of you that are searching :)\u00a0</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If I could offer some advice, it would be:</p>\n<ol><li>Apply everywhere and every day, consistently, no matter how late in the game it is, employers\u00a0are always hiring year-round</li><li>Do company prep\u00a0in-depth to come up with really good questions</li><li>Find a really quiet, distraction-free environment to do interviews</li><li>Prepare well on everything\u00a0including behavioral questions (especially why\u00a0&lt;company x&gt;)</li><li>Be calm and collect your thoughts before answering questions, have a structured approach</li><li>Try to display positivity when answering questions, even if you have no idea where to start</li><li>Be honest about what you know\u00a0and don&#39;t know, humility is also a good trait employers look for\u00a0</li><li>Don\u2019t go in cold, warm-up for the interview beforehand (~ 1 hour), for example, go through a problem you&#39;ve solved before,\u00a0your thought process, etc.</li><li>Follow up regularly\u00a0with companies if you haven&#39;t heard back</li><li>Always ask for feedback, even if it&#39;s standard company policy to not give feedback, it never hurts to ask,\u00a0I&#39;ve actually gotten great feedback this way</li></ol>\n<p></p>\n<p>Hope this helps!</p>", "created": "2019-04-14T06:18:28Z", "subject": "Personal experience/advice on landing an internship/job", "uid_a": "a_0"}], "i_edits": [], "id": "jugjg2295824hp", "is_bookmarked": false, "is_tag_good": false, "my_f